lgo|date= 1916|title= Helgo Zettervall om Lunds domkyrka: en byggnadsbeskrivning i brev|trans-title= Helgo Zettervall on Lund Cathedral: description of a building in letters|url= http://libris.kb.se/bib/10258926|language= Swedish|location= Lund|publisher= }}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category-inline|Lunds domkyrka|Lund Cathedral}}\n* [https://lundsdomkyrka.se/ Official website of the cathedral]\n* [http://www.alvin-portal.org/alvin/view.jsf?pid=alvin-record%3A14714&dswid=3243 Digitised copy of the ''Necrologium Lundense'', with information about the book and its contents in English]\n* [http://www.alvin-portal.org/alvin/view.jsf?pid=alvin-record%3A13276&dswid=7054 Digitised copy of the ''Liber daticus vetustior'', with information about the book and its contents in English]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3LzcTh1FX5k3C8Y4EJI0Ew YouTube channel of the cathedral]\n\n{{Churches in Scania}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1145]]\n[[Category:12th-century churches]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Lund]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in pre-Reformation Sweden]]\n[[Category:Lutheran cathedrals in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Romanesque architecture in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Lund]]\n[[Category:Coronation church buildings]]\n[[Category:Churches in Sk\u00e5ne County]]\n[[Category:Churches in the Diocese of Lund]]\n", "name_user": "EGL1234", "label": "safe", "comment": "Clarification", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lund_Cathedral"}
{"title_page": "Kajiado County", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{distinguish|Kajiado}}\n{{Infobox settlement \n|official_name      = Kajiado County\n|image_skyline      =\n|image_size         = \n|image_caption      = Emali-Oloitokitok Highway\n|image_map          = Kajiado County in Kenya.svg\n|map_caption        = Location in Kenya\n|image_flag         = Flag of Kajiado County.png\n|flag_size          = 130px\n|image_shield       = Coat of Arms of Kajiado County.png\n|shield_size        = 100px\n|settlement_type    = [[Counties of Kenya|County]]\n|subdivision_type   = Country\n|subdivision_name   = {{flag|Kenya}}\n|coordinates        = \n|seat_type          = Capital \n|seat               = [[Kajiado]]\n|largest_town       = [[Ngong, Kenya|Ngong]]\n|lOther_towns       = [[Kitengela]]\n|established_title  = Formed\n|established_date   = March 4th 2013\n|leader_title       = [[County Governors of Kenya|Governor]]\n|leader_name        = [[Joseph Ole Lenku]]\n|timezone           = [[East Africa Time|EAT]] \n|utc_offset         = +3\n|area_total_km2     = 21,292.7\n|area_land_km2      = \n|area_water_km2     =\n|population_as_of   = 2019\n|population_total   = 1,117,840<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/36672705/Kenya-Census-2009|title=Kenya Census 2009 - Census - Kenya|author=|date=|website=Scribd|accessdate=20 April 2018}}</ref>\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|elevation_m        = \n|blank_name         =\n|blank_info         =\n|website            = [https://www.kajiado.go.ke kajiado.go.ke]\n|footnotes          =\n}}\n\n'''Kajiado County''' is a [[Counties of Kenya|county]] in the former [[Rift Valley Province]] of [[Kenya]]. As of 2019, Kajiado county spanned an area of 21,292.7&nbsp;km\u00b2, with a recorded population of 1,117,840. <sup>[http://www.statoids.com/yke.html]</sup> The county borders [[Nairobi]] and extends to the [[Tanzania]] border further south. The county capital is [[Kajiado]] town, but the largest town is [[Ngong, Kenya|Ngong]]. Its main tourist attraction is its wildlife.\n\n==Administration==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| '''Local authorities (councils)''' \n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| \n|-\n!Authority  \n!Type \n!Population\n!Urban pop. size\n|-\n| [[Kajiado]] || Town || 12,204 || 9,128\n|-\n| Olkejuado  || County || 393,850 || 71,223\n|-\n| ''Total''  || - || ''406,054'' || ''80,351''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| {{smaller|* 1999 census. Source: [http://treasury.go.ke/cbs.go.ke/pdf/authority.pdf]}}\n|}\n\nThe county is divided into seven administrative divisions. The newly created [[Isinya]] division is not included in the following table based on 1999 census:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| '''Administrative divisions''' \n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| \n|-\n!Division  \n!Population*\n!Urban pop.*\n!Headquarters\n|-\n| Central || 69,402 || 16,444 || [[Kajiado]]\n|-\n| Loitokitok || 95,430 || 7,495 || \n[[Loitokitok]]\n|-\n| Magadi || 20,112 || 0 || [[Magadi, Kenya|Magadi]]\n|-\n| Mashuru || 35,666 || 2,248 || [[Mashuru]]\n|-\n| Namanga  || 35,673 || 5,503 || [[Namanga]]\n|-\n| Ngong || 149,771 || 20,657 || [[Ngong, Kenya|Ngong]] \n|-\n| ''Total'' || ''406,054'' || ''38,299'' || - \n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"| {{smaller|* 1999 census. Sources: [http://www.cck.go.ke/html/final_annex1_cover_status.pdf],  [http://www.ilri.cgiar.org/html/Urban%20Poverty%20all%20Kenya%20Province%20through%20Location%20Final.xls], }}\n|}\n\n===Constituencies===\n*[[Kajiado Central Constituency]]\n*[[Kajiado North Constituency]]\n*[[Kajiado South Constituency]]\n*[[Kajiado East Constituency]]\n*[[Kajiado West Constituency]]\n\n==Services==\n{{Bar chart\n| float       = center\n| title       = Stats for Kajiado County\n| table_width = 70\n| bar_width   = 50 <!-- must be an unformatted number -->\n| data_max    = 100<!-- Upper bound on the values in the data fields -->\n| label_type  = County\n| data_type   = {{center|Stats for the County (Percent)}}\n| label1     